data.name: EducationDCSubDescA
data.value: Teachers, students and parents use iPad and applications to connect, communicate and collaborate on assignments, student behavior and more—anytime, anywhere.

data.name: EducationDCSubDescB
data.value: A teacher uses iPad to assign work, give feedback, communicate with parents and post grades. When he leaves for the day, he simply takes his device to catch up on grading and lesson plans at home.

data.value: When it comes to deploying mobile devices throughout your school, Education lets you easily match devices to students or classes, assign apps and more so you can:

data.name: EducationMLFSubDescA
data.value: Keeping students engaged and focused can be a challenge for all educators. Digital learning is fun and interactive. Without even realizing it, students can gain knowledge, become better learners and develop skills, all while having fun.

data.name: EducationMLFSubDescB
data.value: Students in classrooms leverage amazing applications purpose built for education to help them become better learners, focus on specific disciplines (like STEM or Language Arts), and practice effective communication. Students have fun with learning games, gamification, and unlimited access to content related to topics that are of particular interest to them.

data.name: EducationMLFSubDescC
data.value: Going beyond traditional curriculums and subjects helps students find new passions and learn to think in creative ways. Applications challenge students to learn and create in new ways, creating new interests and nurturing confidence.

data.name: EducationMPOSSubDescA
data.value: Retail employees and managers need to be able to serve customers from anywhere in the store. Whether providing product information, performing a price check, or making a sale, being able to move throughout the location is critical. As more customers demand high speed retail, mobile points of sale are becoming absolute necessities.

data.name: EducationMPOSSubDescB
data.value: Employees are no longer stuck at a cash wrap with mobile points of sale. Able to handle traditional POS functions on the go, employees can interact with customers and perform other job duties on the floor in between sales in campus bookstores, cafes, stadium concession stands, ticket windows and more.

data.name: EducationMPOSSubDescC
data.value: For line busting, employees can become points of sale from any location when cashier backup is needed. Customers picking up just a few items can be quickly out of the store. And, since points of sale have moved beyond the traditional cash wrap, it is easy to scale the points of sale with extra employees and devices for peak times or seasons.

data.name: EducationMPOSSubDescD
data.value: By eliminating or reducing stationary points of sale, retailers reclaim floor space for additional merchandise, expanded cross merchandising, interactive experiences, lounge areas to encourage lingering in stores—the possibilities are endless.

data.name: ExplicitMailClientPolicySecurityMessage
data.value:
This compliance policy allows you to restrict email access to a set of email clients. The device email client displayed on the Email Dashboard is reported by the device when it attempts to sync for email. Wildcard (*) characters may be used to select all records that match a given string or substring.
Policies are evaluated in the following order: Discovered, Custom.

data.name: ExplicitUserEmailPolicyHelpBox
data.value:
This compliance policy allows you to restrict access to a set of users. Note that the username as displayed on the Email Dashboard is reported by the device when it attempts to sync for email. If User Group is chosen from the User Type dropdown, the action selected will apply to all users within that User Group. Additionally, wildcard (*) characters may be used to select all records that match a given string or sub-string.
Policies will be evaluated in the following order: AirWatch Account User / Discovered > User Group > Custom.
